Introduction

SUPERX is an upcoming two-member boy group under Nature Space, formerly known as IBZ during their early pre-debut phase and later rebranded as VI'ENX. The group first introduced themselves in February 2023, with the launch of SNS accounts under the name IBZ. In April 2023, they adopted the name VI'ENX and released their pre-debut digital single "On My Way" on April 16. Despite their promising start, the group experienced significant changes in 2024, with the departure of Wonjin after his contract was terminated, along with the presumed exits of Uin and Younghoon following their removal from the group’s social media accounts.

The remaining members, JN and Yeung, continued their journey by competing in JTBC’s survival show Project 7 in October 2024, where they ranked 49th and 47th, respectively, before being eliminated in episode 8. In December 2024, Nature Space rebranded the group’s SNS accounts as SUPERX, signaling a fresh start for the duo. While their official debut date remains unannounced, excitement is growing around their new direction and future plans.
